# Firebase Configuration
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_firebase_api_key_here
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project_id.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id_here
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project_id.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_messaging_sender_id_here
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_firebase_app_id_here

# Google Analytics (Optional - only if you want analytics tracking)
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=your_measurement_id_here

# Google APIs Configuration (Required for Classroom and Calendar APIs)
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env
# 2. Replace all the placeholder values with your actual configuration

# Firebase Config (from Firebase Console > Project Settings > General > Your apps):
# 3. Get VITE_FIREBASE_* values from Firebase Console
# 4. Make sure to enable Authentication with Google provider
# 5. Enable Firestore Database

# Google APIs Config (from Google Cloud Console > APIs & Services > Credentials):
# 6. Get VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID from your OAuth 2.0 Client ID
# 7. Make sure APIs are enabled: Classroom, Calendar, People APIs
# 8. Configure OAuth consent screen and authorized domains

# Optional:
# 9. If you want Google Analytics, enable Analytics in Firebase and add MEASUREMENT_ID
